l communication and the ability to make presentations before members of the legal profession, the public, and staff;Ability and skill in visioning, strategic planning, proactive community engagement and project implementation;Demonstrated ability to lead, plan, organize, coordinate and manage the staff and programs of a small organization;Ability to articulate the Society’s vision in the area of Access to Justice, and develop and maintain effective working relationships with similar organizations;Demonstrated ability to analyze, prepare and manage a comprehensive budget;Ability to develop and identify creative solutions and opportunities to increase available resources;Ability to analyze complex problems and situations and develop and implement effective solutions. Qualifications Education: Masters Degree in Library or Information Sciences, or a Library Technician Diploma plus five years experience in a library with increasing levels of responsibility Experience: Minimum five years’ progressively responsible experience in library services, preferably in a law library. Must pass a Criminal Record check. Salary range: $65,000-85,000/year The Manitoba Law Library believes in supporting our team by offering a comprehensive compensation package including a competitive salary, pension, group benefits package, career development and training opportunities and a positive work-life balance philosophy. We recognize that diverse opinions, abilities, identities, cultures and languages in our profession and workplace are a critical foundation to an effective and equitable society and encourage all qualified candidates to apply. The Manitoba Law Library Inc. welcomes applications from people with disabilities.Disability accommodations are available upon request. To Apply: Please submit a resume and cover letter by 5:00 p.m. CST, February 26, 2024 to: Karen Sawatzky Director of Legal Resources ksawatzky@lawsociety.mb.ca To learn more visit https://lawlibrary.ca/. The Manitoba Law 