Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Copyright &amp; Institutional Repository Technician Victoria , BC Description For more information and to apply to this position please visit our careers website : https://camosun.peopleadmin.ca/postings/6585GENERAL STATEMENTReporting to the Director, Learning Services, with minimal supervision, the Copyright &amp; Institutional Repository Technician provides copyright information and advice to the college community to ensure materials in all formats (print, digital, media) used by the college community are compliant with copyright legislation and with the college’s copyright policy and fair dealing directive. This position also completes technical tasks related to the institutional repository (Arca) to preserve the college’s archival materials and digital publications.TYPICAL DUTIESProvides copyright information and guidance to faculty developing instructional materials, including open education resources; provides related oversight to the application of the college’s fair dealing directive;Reviews all course-packs to determine whether included materials fall within compliance of the college’s copyright policy and fair dealing directive; maintains records of the use of copyright materials in course packs;Upon request by Supervisor or faculty, reviews materials placed on D2L, course websites for determining if material falls within fall within compliance of the college’s copyright policy and fair dealing directive;Responds to queries from faculty, students and staff about copyright, fair dealing, open access and other related issues;Alerts the Director, Learning Services of possible infringement cases and recommends changes needed procedures to help prevent similar occurrences;Maintains a database of terms of use for licensed library content and ensures the library website provides accurate information for each resource;In collaboration with librarian develops and maintains the Copyright online guide; assists in providing information and awareness on issues related to copyright, including promoting the use of open resources, fair dealing and appropriate attribution and citation;Maintains handouts and copyright notices used in applicable public locations at the college;Upon request seeks copyright permission for the use of copyrighted material from the rights holder; processes payments and maintains records of copyright permissions sought and retained;Collaborates with the Bookstore, Print &amp; Graphic Services in the implementation of efficient and effective copyright procedures for course materialsProvides technical support for the institutional repository, including updating and maintaining content and metadata in established templates; troubleshoots technical issues within the repository in collaboration with the librarian and/or Supervisor;Reviews Arca content to ensure objects have the necessary licensees and approvals for inclusion in the repository; and documents applicable workflow related to Arca;Contributes to the development of education information on copyright procedures for faculty and staff;Participates in communities of practices and other educational opportunities to maintain knowledge and keep up-to-date with trends and developments in the educational resource, copyright and open access field as relates to job duties;Performs other related duties similar in scope and complexity.QUALIFACATIONSA two-year diploma in Library Technician and four years work experience in either post-secondary library or library/archive which include experience in copyright clearance, content licensing or institutional repositories or an equivalent combination of education and experience.Knowledge and understanding of copyright, open licensing, fair dealing and related intellectual property issues;Knowledge of standards and procedures related to institutional repositories;Ability to work independently, to initiate and complete tasks with minimal directionAbility to analyze complex and variable situational problems and apply critical thinking and judgment and conflict resolution techniques to resolve issuesExcellent written and verbal communication skills to deal effectively and professionally with, faculty, staff, administrators, students and the general publicAttention to detail and high regard for accuracy; proficient with record keeping and data entryIn depth knowledge of the Microsoft Office suite, with particular expertise it the use of Excel and AccessStrong organizational skills, including time management and prioritizationFor more information and to apply to this position please visit our careers website : https://camosun.peopleadmin.ca/postings/6585 Compensation $31.32 - $33.43 per hour Closes: 22 February, 2024 Camosun College Victoria , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
