Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Children and Teens Librarian I: Full-time (Permanent) Woodstock , ON Description WOODSTOCK PUBLIC LIBRARY INTERNAL/EXTERNAL JOB POSTING 2024-01 Children &amp; Teens Librarian I:Full-time (Permanent) DATE: February 7, 2024 JOB TITLE: Children &amp; Teens Librarian CLASSIFICATION: Reference Librarian I HOURS OF WORK: Thirty-five (35) hours per week Schedule is subject to change and is not negotiable May include evenings, Saturdays and Sundays NATURE OF POSITION: Reporting to the Public Services Supervisor, this position will provide public service leadership by guiding the development, planning and implementation of programs and services to families, children and teens. Responsible for monitoring trends in children’s and teen’s services and translating them into timely opportunities.Adopts an energetic and team-oriented approach to presenting programs for and with teens so that they educate, inform and inspire. Develops and maintains effective relationships with schools, community groups, agencies and nonprofits that target teens in order to plan and deliver programs and services that meet local teen needs and interests.Makes recommendations for service improvements and workflow changes. Provides information and readers’ advisory services to the public. Manages the selection, deselection and planning for assigned library collections. QUALIFICATIONS: Masters Degree in Library Science from an ALA accredited library school.Two years of relevant experience delivering services to children and teens in a public library environment.Demonstrated experience planning, delivering and evaluating programming for children and teens.Demonstrated experience planning, delivering and evaluating STEAM programming for children and teens.Experience in community outreach to families, children and teens.Experience following emerging trends and developments in children’s and teen librarianship.Knowledge of print and digital information services and resources.Experience in library selection, deselection, and collection planning.Excellent interpersonal, customer, and communication skills. DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILTIES: Responsible for the research, development, planning, implementation and evaluation of children’s and teen’s programs and services. Identify, plan and initiate community outreach programming for families, children and teens.Maintain current knowledge of trends in servicing children and teens through review of literature, networking, exploration of online sources and attending training opportunities both in and outside the library. Incorporate STEAM philosophy into programming and services for children and teens.Demonstrate customer service excellence in the delivery of reader’s advisory service and in response to information requests from the public.Instruct the public in the use of library resources, facilities and equipment.Manage the selection, deselection and planning for assigned juvenile and young adult library collections.Prepare reading lists, guides and other finding aids. Assume the duties of a person in charge as required.Perform related duties as assigned. SALARY RATE AND RANGE: $37.10/hr to $40.57/hr (2023 rates) APPLICATION DEADLINE: 4:00 pm, February 16, 2024 This is a bargaining unit position, CUPE Local 1146-Library Unit. Library Unit employees will first be given consideration for this vacancy followed by other applicants. Interested persons are requested to submit a cover letter and resume to: Lori Peixoto Administrative Assistant Woodstock Public Library 445 Hunter Street Woodstock ON N4S 4G7 lpeixoto@mywpl.ca Only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Personal information is collected in accordance with the Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Personal Privacy Act. The Woodstock Public Library Board is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer. Accommodations are available for all parts of the recruitment process. Applicants need to make their needs known in advance. Compensation 37.10/hr to 40.57/hr Closes: 16 February, 2024 Woodstock Public Library Woodstock , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
