Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Public Services Manager Swift Current , SK Description 110 11th Ave NW, Swift Current Phone: (306) 773-3186 Website: https://chinooklibrary.ca Full-time Permanent Position Chinook Regional Library Headquarters Job Title: Public Services Manager Job Classification: Management Job Summary: Reporting to the Regional Director, the Public Services Manager is responsible for supervising the operation of the Swift Current Public Library, and together with other members of the management team, for coordinating and contributing to regional projects, and programs. DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES: Responsible to the Library Director and the Swift Current Library Board for the operations of the Swift Current Public Library. Participates in hiring, and staffing decisions for the Swift Current Public Library, and Regional Headquarters. Supervises staff at the Swift Current Public Library and provides annual performance evaluations for the full-time, permanent, employees. Adheres to an annual budget, and is able to report monthly on operational spending at the Swift Current Public Library, as well as on the projects and programs under their supervision. Work with community organizations and institutions to meet specific needs and to cooperate with the Chinook Regional Library in carrying out region-wide activities. Participates in the compilation of reports and statistics. Acts as Secretary to the Swift Current Library Board and all committees of that Board. Prepares and implements, in consultation with the Swift Current Library Board, a budget for events, programming, and other expenses. Works with the Regional Director and management team in implementing the goals of the Chinook Regional Library. REQUIRED: A MLIS degree from an ALA accredited Library Science Program. ASSETS: Knowledge and interest in integrated library systems. Experience supervising staff. Ability to organize and plan effectively. Ability to work effectively in a team environment. Knowledge of typical public library procedures and best practices. Physical Requirements: Ability to lift, carry or move library materials weighing 5 – 15 kilograms on a regular basis Ability to reach a range of shelves between 5 cm and 200 cm above floor Others: Current Criminal Record Check Current Driver’s License This position is open to candidates of all levels of experience and skill, provided that they approach the position with energy, a positive attitude, and an interest in learning. The incumbent will enjoy support from a large, professional, and experienced, management team. The Chinook Regional Library is engaged in several interesting projects, and is engaged in partnerships with many other agencies. The incumbent will have the option to participate within their aptitude and skill-set. Hours: Salary is based on an average 37.5-hour work-week. Salary: Starting at $60,000 annually, with regular increases based on skill and productivity Posted: January 15th, 2024Closing date: open until filled Please submit cover letter and resume to the address below: Jake Marion, Director Email:director@chinook.lib.sk.ca Compensation $60,000 Closes: 22 April, 2024 Chinook Regional Library Swift Current , SK Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
