Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Librarian, Yellowhead Regional Library Spruce Grove , AB Description Description YRL is seeking an energetic, proactive, customer-focused candidate to provide professional expertise, guidance, and support to YRL’s member public and school libraries with the Library Development Services (LDS) team. Responding to the needs of library staff and boards, this position contributes to YRL’s goal of ensuring that members have sustainable and effective library service. The LDS Librarian plays a significant role in portraying a positive image of YRL by establishing strong and respectful relationships with the staff at our member libraries and is often the first point of contact for support to member libraries on all matters related to library operations and management. Requirements Broad tasks include, but are not limited to: Provision of professional support and expertise to member libraries in all areas of library management and operations.Responsible for planning and implementing training opportunities using a variety of tools and frameworks.Contributes to the development and management of value-added and shared resources, such as regional collections, programs, and services.Contributes to the achievement of service goals by providing workplans, proposals and the development of departmental initiatives.Represents YRL at regional and provincial levels.Cooperates with colleagues for the achievement of YRL’s goals and strategic plan. Qualifications MLIS from an ALA-accredited institution.One year of related library work experience.Excellent communication and presentation skills, including delivery of training and presentations in a variety of formats and venues. Demonstrated ability to build relationships with a diverse population, balance multiple processes and priorities, adapt to changing environments, work independently, and manage time to ensure project completion.Knowledge of legislation impacting public library operations in Alberta. Proficiency in a modern, technological library environment.Proficiency in evaluation and impact analysis to inform decision making an asset.Experience or understanding of adult learners and change processes an asset.Experience with statistical reporting, technical support and needs assessments an asset.A valid Class 5 Alberta driver’s licence and the aptitude for travel to rural and outlying communities.A commitment to upholding the Canadian Federation of Library Associations statements on Intellectual Freedom and Diversity and Inclusion. About Us Formed in 1971, YRL is headquartered in Spruce Grove, and serves a population of more than 300,000 through a network of 85+ member public and school libraries. Find out more at yrl.ab.ca. Compensation The salary starts at $2,336 biweekly based on the 2024 salary grid and a 35-hour work week. Apply Interested candidates should send a cover letter, resume and the contact information of three (3) references to Laurie Haak at lhaak@yrl.ab.ca by Sunday, February 18 with the subject line Librarian. By applying for this position, you consent to the collection, use and necessary disclosure of the personal information provided during the application and selection process. We thank all applicants however, only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $2,336 biweekly Closes: 18 February, 2024 Yellowhead Regional Library Spruce Grove , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
